00:18:00,979 --> 00:18:02,689
It's not working.

238
00:18:10,214 --> 00:18:11,589
What's that?

239
00:18:11,589 --> 00:18:12,590
Senior,

240
00:18:12,591 --> 00:18:14,033
do you see that?

241
00:18:14,033 --> 00:18:15,635
What can that be?

242
00:18:16,954 --> 00:18:18,079
The smell...

243
00:18:18,079 --> 00:18:20,074
It's dangerous. Run!

244
00:18:43,630 --> 00:18:44,760
[Goo Yeong]

245
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:47,859
Hello?

246
00:18:49,987 --> 00:18:53,281
Yi Kang and Hyun Jo? They're not back yet.

247
00:18:53,841 --> 00:18:55,283
Yeah.

248
00:18:56,744 --> 00:18:59,437
All right. I'll try to radio them.

249
00:19:00,330 --> 00:19:01,865
What was that?

250
00:19:06,562 --> 00:19:09,939
Yi Kang and Hyun Jo went to Black Bridge Valley,

251
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:12,033
but they're not back yet.

252
00:19:16,597 --> 00:19:18,389
These punks!

253
00:19:18,389 --> 00:19:21,368
I told them not to go there, how many times?

254
00:19:23,479 --> 00:19:25,288
But, Captain.

255
00:19:25,288 --> 00:19:29,959
The one who posted the video from Black Bridge Valley was found by the roadway.

256
00:19:29,959 --> 00:19:32,420
And he's been saying something strange.

257
00:19:32,421 --> 00:19:35,573
That he saw ghost lights there.

258
00:19:41,570 --> 00:19:43,924
Haedong Ranger Station, Control Room.

259
00:19:43,924 --> 00:19:45,708
No, we need to go.

260
00:19:45,708 --> 00:19:47,636
Seo Yi Kang, where are you?

261
00:19:50,630 --> 00:19:53,466
Maybe their radio broke.

262
00:19:53,466 --> 00:19:56,253
Or maybe they're on their way down.

263
00:20:10,667 --> 00:20:12,168
This way.

264
00:20:21,630 --> 00:20:24,170
[Seo Yi Kang]

265
00:20:36,510 --> 00:20:39,929
Call me if they don't return by 6.00. And keep trying to reach them.

266
00:20:39,929 --> 00:20:42,107
They'll be all right.

267
00:20:42,850 --> 00:20:44,934
It's Senior Yi Kang.

268
00:20:44,934 --> 00:20:46,936
Black Bridge Valley is different.

269
00:20:46,936 --> 00:20:50,090
You've heard a saying, "mountains make people hallucinate." Right?

270
00:20:51,191 --> 00:20:53,460
Black Bridge Valley is that kind of place.

271
00:20:57,420 --> 00:20:59,110
[1991]

272
00:20:59,110 --> 00:21:02,474
So, when can we start using the well?

273
00:21:02,474 --> 00:21:05,262
Not for a while.

274
00:21:05,263 --> 00:21:07,574
We can't drink rotten water.

275
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:12,361
I'm sick of traveling like this to get water.

276
00:21:12,361 --> 00:21:14,322
It won't kill you.

277
00:21:14,974 --> 00:21:18,718
- See you later.
- Okay, see you.

278
00:21:18,718 --> 00:21:21,988
- Be careful. It's slippery.
- Okay.

279
00:22:49,977 --> 00:22:52,353
Someone's been missing?

280
00:22:52,353 --> 00:22:54,105
For how long?

281
00:22:54,105 --> 00:22:56,649
Since yesterday, when she went up to get water from the stream.

282
00:22:56,649 --> 00:22:59,735
There were buckets and bloodstains near the stream,

283
00:22:59,735 --> 00:23:03,406
so I thoroughly looked around.

284
00:23:03,406 --> 00:23:05,550
But she's nowhere to be seen.

285
00:23:06,368 --> 00:23:08,887
It's all because of him.

286
00:23:09,663 --> 00:23:12,574
If he hadn't ruined the well,

287
00:23:15,127 --> 00:23:19,356
my wife wouldn't have gone to get water.

288
00:23:19,965 --> 00:23:21,966
We'll find her.

289
00:23:21,966 --> 00:23:23,592
I promise.

290
00:23:23,592 --> 00:23:27,063
So give us some time. And please don't worry.

291
00:23:40,944 --> 00:23:43,487
Mrs. Kim Seong Sook.

292
00:23:43,487 --> 00:23:47,283
- Mrs. Kim Seong Sook!
- Mrs. Kim Seong Sook!

293
00:23:47,283 --> 00:23:50,095
Mrs. Kim Seong Sook.

294
00:23:54,933 --> 00:23:59,354
Mrs. Kim Seong Sook!

295
00:24:04,760 --> 00:24:06,218
Mrs. Kim Seong Sook!

296
00:24:06,218 --> 00:24:11,049
Even park rangers often get lost near Black Bridge Village.

297
00:24:13,560 --> 00:24:17,372
Sometimes seemingly safe paths lead to cliffs,

298
00:24:18,231 --> 00:24:20,877
and trails disappear suddenly.

299
00:24:22,235 --> 00:24:26,173
The mountain is making us hallucinate.

300
00:24:27,032 --> 00:24:29,509
We must stay alert.

301
00:25:29,402 --> 00:25:31,103
Check around those trees, too.

302
00:25:31,103 --> 00:25:33,548
Mrs. Kim Seong Sook!

303
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:37,827
Mrs. Kim Seong Sook!

304
00:26:32,032 --> 00:26:33,967
Her pulse is very weak!

305
00:27:05,774 --> 00:27:07,909
Was she found here?

306
00:27:09,778 --> 00:27:12,439
She had fallen next to that tree.

307
00:27:55,657 --> 00:27:57,440
It's all because of me.

308
00:27:58,994 --> 00:28:04,253
I heard she could have survived if we had been a little quicker.

309
00:28:05,725 --> 00:28:09,086
I passed by that tree several times.

310
00:28:09,086 --> 00:28:11,873
Had I found her a little earlier...

311
00:28:13,900 --> 00:28:15,968
Let's go in.

312
00:28:15,968 --> 00:28:18,204
We should see her off.

313
00:28:38,110 --> 00:28:41,240
[2019]

314
00:28:45,999 --> 00:28:48,568
So what are those?

315
00:28:48,568 --> 00:28:51,378
People say they see ghost lights

316
00:28:51,378 --> 00:28:55,108
on dark and foggy nights like this on the mountain.

317
00:28:57,010 --> 00:28:59,136
Is that really a ghost light?

318
00:28:59,136 --> 00:29:01,047
Of course not.

319
00:29:09,439 --> 00:29:11,449
Don't you remember this smell?

320
00:29:13,193 --> 00:29:15,361
What's this smell?

321
00:29:15,361 --> 00:29:18,322
Dog odor combined with ammonia.

322
00:29:18,322 --> 00:29:19,990
It's a bear.

323
00:29:19,990 --> 00:29:22,068
Bear? That's...?

324
00:29:24,412 --> 00:29:28,983
I heard wild animals' eyes look like that, reflected in the light.

325
00:29:28,983 --> 00:29:32,336
That's impossible. I heard Asian black bears hate people.

326
00:29:32,336 --> 00:29:36,150
Also, they aren't aggressive, as long as we don't attack them first.

327
00:29:37,008 --> 00:29:39,326
I've never seen anything like this before.

328
00:29:39,326 --> 00:29:42,763
Even if they aren't aggressive, bears are the wildest of wild beasts.

329
00:29:42,763 --> 00:29:46,433
They're over two meters tall and weigh over 100kg.

330
00:29:46,433 --> 00:29:51,313
I don't know why they're so provoked, but I'm sure it's more dangerous than a ghost light.

331
00:29:51,313 --> 00:29:54,258
- Pass me your walkie.
- Yes.

332
00:30:01,991 --> 00:30:04,511
The battery's dead.

333
00:30:20,218 --> 00:30:22,595
This is a "no signal" area.

334
00:30:43,742 --> 00:30:45,752
We're trapped.

335
00:30:53,470 --> 00:30:57,520
[1991]

336
00:31:19,360 --> 00:31:20,878
Mayor!

337
00:31:22,739 --> 00:31:25,617
Cable cars or whatever...

338
00:31:25,617 --> 00:31:27,410
I can't leave this place now.

339
00:31:27,410 --> 00:31:30,370
We're not here because of the cable cars.

340
00:31:30,370 --> 00:31:33,374
Most of the villagers have left.

341
00:31:33,374 --> 00:31:36,002
The park decided to demolish the village, too.

342
00:31:36,002 --> 00:31:39,788
- Why don't you move to...
- I'm not leaving!

343
00:32:00,109 --> 00:32:03,143
How have you been? Did you eat?

344
00:32:03,143 --> 00:32:06,908
Dad keeps saying he sees things.

345
00:32:06,908 --> 00:32:08,910
What do you mean?

346
00:32:08,910 --> 00:32:11,454
He says he sees ghost lights.

347
00:32:11,454 --> 00:32:14,399
There's no such thing. He saw wrong.

348
00:32:14,399 --> 00:32:18,019
No! There is. I saw them, too.

349
00:32:20,797 --> 00:32:22,890
Let's call it a day.

350
00:32:25,760 --> 00:32:27,303
Yes, sir.

351
00:32:52,203 --> 00:32:54,022
- This way.
[2019]

352
00:32:54,022 --> 00:32:57,609
Why are you trying to meet him at this point?

353
00:32:57,609 --> 00:32:59,669
Are you charging him a fine?

354
00:32:59,669 --> 00:33:02,572
- How's his condition?
- They say he's much better.

355
00:33:02,572 --> 00:33:04,190
That's the one.

356
00:33:18,146 --> 00:33:19,064
Hello?

357
00:33:19,064 --> 00:33:21,900
So, on my way from Deokseoryeong to Black Bridge Valley,

358
00:33:21,900 --> 00:33:24,027
- there was some woman.
- Excuse me?

359
00:33:24,027 --> 00:33:26,370
Anyway, I've made the call.

360
00:33:29,081 --> 00:33:30,799
What did you say?

361
00:33:32,430 --> 00:33:34,190
About what?

362
00:33:34,193 --> 00:33:36,764
Someone was at Deokseoryeong?

363
00:33:38,041 --> 00:33:40,501
No, well... It was her fault.

364
00:33:40,501 --> 00:33:43,254
Why did she go up there when she clearly was not in good shape?

365
00:33:43,254 --> 00:33:47,172
Don't tell me you left a lost person there and came down on your own.

366
00:33:47,172 --> 00:33:50,945
Could you let the rangers know that I'm here?

367
00:33:50,945 --> 00:33:52,487
Jeez, lady.

368
00:33:52,488 --> 00:33:55,642
Do you want me to take myself in for illegal hiking?

369
00:33:55,642 --> 00:33:59,412
I'll make a report on my way down, once I'm done with my business.

370
00:34:03,092 --> 00:34:05,135
Where was it?

371
00:34:06,135 --> 00:34:09,681
Well, I... I was busy, too.

372
00:34:15,270 --> 00:34:17,171
Where the hell was it?

373
00:34:26,230 --> 00:34:29,133
When will they leave?

374
00:34:30,677 --> 00:34:34,438
How would I know?

375
00:34:35,374 --> 00:34:37,708
I'm sorry.

376
00:34:39,129 --> 00:34:43,548
But... I didn't expect a place like this in the mountains.

377
00:34:43,548 --> 00:34:46,967
It must have been a secret hideout for the red commies.

378
00:34:47,953 --> 00:34:50,113
What? There's a pole.

379
00:34:50,113 --> 00:34:52,615
It must be one left behind by the illegal hikers.

380
00:34:52,615 --> 00:34:55,551
More like crampons. Pretty serious.

381
00:35:10,283 --> 00:35:11,900
- Whoa!
- What was that?

382
00:35:11,901 --> 00:35:13,360
- Senior...
- What's up with you?

383
00:35:13,361 --> 00:35:16,022
There's someone here.

384
00:35:21,244 --> 00:35:23,703
Her breathing is too weak. She has serious hypothermia.

385
00:35:23,704 --> 00:35:25,924
We must hurry up and get her to a hospital.

386
00:35:29,110 --> 00:35:30,878
Will you be okay?

387
00:35:33,448 --> 00:35:37,525
Do I have a choice? We must go.

388
00:36:06,731 --> 00:36:08,065
There's been a missing report.

389
00:36:08,065 --> 00:36:11,827
Please gather at the restricted trail entrance in Deokseoryeong.

390
00:36:13,988 --> 00:36:16,574
I called each shelter and the rangers on their day off.

391
00:36:16,574 --> 00:36:19,177
Any news from Yi Kang and Hyun Jo?

392
00:36:20,119 --> 00:36:21,445
No.

393
00:36:22,423 --> 00:36:26,559
But... those two aren't the only ones at Black Bridge Valley.

394
00:36:54,714 --> 00:36:58,007
Senior, we're back again.

395
00:37:00,201 --> 00:37:02,069
You all right?

396
00:37:04,480 --> 00:37:05,931
What's that?

397
00:37:05,932 --> 00:37:07,057
Ah, honestly.

398
00:37:07,058 --> 00:37:10,636
What happened? We couldn't reach you.

399
00:37:10,636 --> 00:37:12,731
Who's that?

400
00:37:15,967 --> 00:37:18,094
- And what's that?
- Get her on your back.

401
00:37:18,094 --> 00:37:20,412
Quickly!

402
00:37:22,680 --> 00:37:24,860
What is that?

403
00:37:24,867 --> 00:37:27,269
- Get on.
- Hurry up!

404
00:37:27,269 --> 00:37:28,980
What the heck? What is that?

405
00:37:28,980 --> 00:37:30,664
Hurry up! Hurry!

406
00:37:32,625 --> 00:37:34,318
In here.

407
00:37:34,318 --> 00:37:36,611
Watch your step.

408
00:37:36,611 --> 00:37:38,238
On two.

409
00:37:40,057 --> 00:37:42,259
What happened?

410
00:37:42,259 --> 00:37:44,036
- She's in a bad state.
- I know.

411
00:37:44,036 --> 00:37:47,206
That's why we were trying so hard to get down, but couldn't find the way out.

412
00:37:47,206 --> 00:37:49,708
Same for us, too.

413
00:37:49,708 --> 00:37:53,103
We kept going around in one direction in the foggy area.

414
00:37:53,104 --> 00:37:56,564
We could only come because of your flashlights.

415
00:37:56,565 --> 00:37:58,942
- What's that thing?
- Bears.

416
00:37:58,943 --> 00:38:01,486
- What?
- What?

417
00:38:01,487 --> 00:38:04,039
Nonsense.

418
00:38:05,274 --> 00:38:09,636
What are you saying? Are we trapped?

419
00:38:09,636 --> 00:38:11,731
Hang on. There must be a way.

420
00:38:11,731 --> 00:38:13,024
A way? What way?

421
00:38:13,024 --> 00:38:15,735
You can't get out because you can't find your way.

422
00:38:15,735 --> 00:38:18,905
- Calm yourself down.
- Don't tell me to calm down.

423
00:38:18,905 --> 00:38:21,574
Why did you come up here in the first place and get us into this?

424
00:38:21,574 --> 00:38:24,884
Did I tell you to come? Go back down then.

425
00:38:24,885 --> 00:38:27,955
- Stop it, both of you.
- Stop what?

426
00:38:27,955 --> 00:38:30,041
The promotion test is only a few days away.

427
00:38:30,041 --> 00:38:33,252
I don't have a second to waste, and what the heck am I doing here?

428
00:38:33,252 --> 00:38:36,714
Did you take a day off only for that? When everyone's busy as hell?

429
00:38:36,714 --> 00:38:40,134
Only? It's something very important for me.

430
00:38:40,134 --> 00:38:42,862
I'm meeting Yang Sun's mother soon for a pre-wedding introduction.

431
00:38:44,038 --> 00:38:48,309
I should at least have a team leader title since I've got nothing else!

432
00:38:48,309 --> 00:38:50,227
Hey, seriously.

433
00:38:50,227 --> 00:38:52,772
Is that something you should say here and now?

434
00:38:52,772 --> 00:38:54,899
Team leader? What's the big deal about the title?

435
00:38:54,899 --> 00:38:57,401
Stop bragging. You're already a team leader.

436
00:38:57,401 --> 00:38:59,779
Do you think it's all fun and games for me?

437
00:38:59,779 --> 00:39:02,698
I've not rested a day since I got promoted.

438
00:39:02,698 --> 00:39:03,798
And now...

439
00:39:05,393 --> 00:39:09,163
I can't use my legs.

440
00:39:09,163 --> 00:39:11,916
I might not be able to walk

441
00:39:11,916 --> 00:39:14,226
if I keep climbing the mountain.

442
00:39:22,802 --> 00:39:25,221
Her condition's gotten worse.

443
00:39:25,221 --> 00:39:27,639
I don't think she can last long.

444
00:39:33,646 --> 00:39:36,565
Park Il Hae. Can you hear me?

445
00:39:36,565 --> 00:39:39,652
- Did you get to Black Bridge Valley?
- Yes, sir.

446
00:39:39,652 --> 00:39:41,112
We met Yi Kang and Hyun Jo.

447
00:39:41,112 --> 00:39:44,407
We got a call about a missing person

448
00:39:44,407 --> 00:39:46,216
between Deokseoryeong and Black Bridge Valley.

449
00:39:46,217 --> 00:39:49,578
Do you mean the woman in a red jacket?

450
00:39:49,578 --> 00:39:52,915
Did you find her? How is she?

451
00:39:52,915 --> 00:39:56,252
She's not good. We must take her to the hospital immediately.

452
00:39:56,252 --> 00:39:59,395
Our situation's not that great either. We can't find our way out.

453
00:39:59,396 --> 00:40:03,525
It's hard to secure a clear view because of the fog, and the GPS is not working.

454
00:40:03,526 --> 00:40:07,821
We don't know why, but the Asian black bears aren't leaving our side.

455
00:40:07,822 --> 00:40:12,050
Yi Kang and Hyun Jo tried to carry the victim down, but they failed.

456
00:40:13,894 --> 00:40:16,088
Let me talk to Yi Kang.

457
00:40:22,094 --> 00:40:23,845
Seo Yi Kang speaking.

458
00:40:23,845 --> 00:40:26,197
You will take the lead and find the way.

459
00:40:26,197 --> 00:40:29,142
You're the fastest, and you know the mountain best.

460
00:40:29,142 --> 00:40:31,328
I'm not confident.

461
00:40:32,580 --> 00:40:34,814
I cannot find the way.

462
00:40:34,814 --> 00:40:38,818
I almost got lost there once, too.

463
00:40:38,818 --> 00:40:41,364
And a missing person ended up dying because of me.

464
00:40:44,742 --> 00:40:47,978
I analyzed the surroundings and found out why.

465
00:40:47,978 --> 00:40:51,915
It was because I was tracing the animal path, not the human one.

466
00:40:51,915 --> 00:40:55,293
I'll take her. You just hurt your knees.

467
00:40:55,293 --> 00:41:00,023
I'll do it. My knees are newer than yours.

468
00:41:00,758 --> 00:41:02,692
The man-made path leads to the village,

469
00:41:02,692 --> 00:41:05,737
but the one the animals have made is in the opposite direction.

470
00:41:05,737 --> 00:41:09,891
If you feel like you're going in circles, go the opposite way, no matter what.

471
00:41:09,891 --> 00:41:14,621
Abandon everything except your headlamps and walkies. Make yourselves as light as possible.

472
00:41:15,289 --> 00:41:17,800
Hyun Jo, you take the front since you can steadily carry her.

473
00:41:17,800 --> 00:41:21,350
Goo Yeong, assist him, and Il Hae, the rear.

474
00:41:25,741 --> 00:41:30,670
You failed when you were in pairs, but now it's four of you.

475
00:41:31,305 --> 00:41:33,607
Trust one another.

476
00:41:35,359 --> 00:41:38,570
Don't worry about anything, just run forward.

477
00:41:38,570 --> 00:41:42,420
Your fellow rangers will watch your back.

478
00:42:09,076 --> 00:42:11,537
Let's go. Run!

479
00:43:00,294 --> 00:43:02,913
What's the matter? What happened?

480
00:43:41,519 --> 00:43:44,396
Please get rid of the trees, too.

481
00:43:50,200 --> 00:43:54,410
[Kim Jae Gyeong]

482
00:43:59,103 --> 00:44:02,047
Had I saved her...

483
00:44:03,999 --> 00:44:06,943
could I have saved this village?

484
00:44:16,871 --> 00:44:21,555
Do you... want to quit this job?

485
00:44:24,336 --> 00:44:26,212
Quitting won't end it.

486
00:44:26,212 --> 00:44:28,965
You'll keep seeing dead people on the mountain,

487
00:44:28,965 --> 00:44:31,467
and only feel guiltier with time.

488
00:44:31,467 --> 00:44:36,381
You can't escape the mountain even if you want to.

489
00:44:36,381 --> 00:44:38,474
With that sympathy in your mind,
[Kim Jae Gyeong]

490
00:44:38,474 --> 00:44:42,061
try harder to save people with all your heart.

491
00:44:42,061 --> 00:44:45,557
That's our job.

492
00:44:47,140 --> 00:44:52,170
[Kim Jae Gyeong]

493
00:45:09,757 --> 00:45:11,817
How's the missing person doing?

494
00:45:12,651 --> 00:45:14,527
They'll save her.

495
00:45:14,527 --> 00:45:17,272
They're different from me.

496
00:46:33,716 --> 00:46:37,570
You come here every year.

497
00:47:02,880 --> 00:47:10,320
[Kim Jae Gyeong]

498
00:47:11,337 --> 00:47:15,331
It's a pleasure to meet you. I'm Jung Goo Yeong.

499
00:47:16,066 --> 00:47:18,468
He's my senior that I've told you about.

500
00:47:18,468 --> 00:47:20,387
Isn't he handsome?

501
00:47:22,823 --> 00:47:26,785
I appreciate everything you do for my daughter.

502
00:47:27,728 --> 00:47:30,063
By the way, how tall are you?

503
00:47:30,063 --> 00:47:33,775
Mom, why would you ask something like that?

504
00:47:36,520 --> 00:47:40,407
Around 170 cm...

505
00:47:40,407 --> 00:47:45,336
171...

506
00:47:49,416 --> 00:47:53,086
This is a gift to the Best Ranger of the Month, Mr. Jung Goo Yeong,

507
00:47:53,086 --> 00:47:57,206
from the chief of the Jirisan National Park.

508
00:47:57,206 --> 00:48:03,284
He will also be paying for your meals today.

509
00:48:03,284 --> 00:48:05,815
Please enjoy.

510
00:48:06,934 --> 00:48:09,769
- The Best Ranger of the Month?
- Yeah.

511
00:48:09,769 --> 00:48:12,021
You must be really good at what you're doing.

512
00:48:12,021 --> 00:48:15,458
Of course, he's an excellent ranger.

513
00:48:15,458 --> 00:48:17,544
Oh, yes.

514
00:48:19,363 --> 00:48:22,357
The flowers are so beautiful.

515
00:48:24,368 --> 00:48:26,119
They're as beautiful as you.

516
00:48:26,119 --> 00:48:30,957
The chief must have meant them for you.

517
00:48:36,438 --> 00:48:37,880
Do you like flowers?

518
00:48:37,880 --> 00:48:39,991
Of course.

519
00:48:41,084 --> 00:48:42,944
They're beautiful.

520
00:48:42,944 --> 00:48:44,450
So pretty.

521
00:48:51,530 --> 00:48:53,671
See? What did I tell you?

522
00:48:53,671 --> 00:48:56,274
I knew he'd come empty-handed for the first meeting.

523
00:48:56,300 --> 00:48:58,500
Things are looking good.

524
00:48:59,443 --> 00:49:02,280
What's the time? We have to patrol the mountain spirit ritual.

525
00:49:05,140 --> 00:49:06,451
What's going on?

526
00:49:06,451 --> 00:49:08,286
Are you still carrying that thing?

527
00:49:08,286 --> 00:49:09,954
Throw it away.

528
00:49:09,954 --> 00:49:13,990
That's up to me. It's mine now since you gave it to me.

529
00:49:15,675 --> 00:49:19,120
Let's go. The ritual must have begun.

530
00:49:21,875 --> 00:49:24,686
He keeps trying to climb up.

531
00:50:17,990 --> 00:50:20,566
- Hello.
- I'm glad you're here.

532
00:50:20,566 --> 00:50:23,194
Have you looked for Asian black bears near Black Bridge Valley?

533
00:50:23,194 --> 00:50:24,278
Of course.

534
00:50:24,278 --> 00:50:27,448
We have No. 35 and her two cubs born this winter.

535
00:50:27,448 --> 00:50:30,451
Are you sure they chased you? They're such sweet babies.

536
00:50:30,451 --> 00:50:32,995
Do you think I made that up? Say something.

537
00:50:32,995 --> 00:50:35,031
It's true.

538
00:50:35,031 --> 00:50:37,024
Maybe you provoked her first.

539
00:50:37,024 --> 00:50:38,568
Are you nuts?

540
00:50:38,568 --> 00:50:40,378
Well, anyhow.

541
00:50:40,378 --> 00:50:43,339
I guess you should thank the bears.

542
00:50:43,339 --> 00:50:46,093
You got to save someone, thanks to them.

543
00:50:49,555 --> 00:50:51,264
Didn't you say you found her while being chased by the bears?

544
00:50:51,264 --> 00:50:52,374
Without a missing report.

545
00:50:52,374 --> 00:50:56,585
It would have been impossible to find her hidden in the rocks on that huge mountain, otherwise.

546
00:50:56,585 --> 00:50:59,313
We saved her, not the bears.

547
00:50:59,313 --> 00:51:01,916
- It was the bears.
- You have no idea how we survived.

548
00:51:01,916 --> 00:51:04,026
- What?
- We nearly died.

549
00:51:04,026 --> 00:51:06,496
- Is that so?
- You're driving me insane.

550
00:51:07,497 --> 00:51:09,323
That doesn't make any sense.

551
00:51:09,323 --> 00:51:12,168
What do you mean, thanks to the bears?

552
00:51:13,562 --> 00:51:15,980
They guided you all the way there.

553
00:51:15,980 --> 00:51:17,832
To find that person.

554
00:51:17,832 --> 00:51:20,935
Guide us? You're insane.

555
00:51:25,190 --> 00:51:26,982
Well, that's a surprise.

556
00:51:26,982 --> 00:51:30,177
Why don't you answer your phone?

557
00:51:30,177 --> 00:51:32,430
I was going to call back after work.

558
00:51:32,430 --> 00:51:35,133
Didn't you say you were coming home this week?

559
00:51:39,121 --> 00:51:42,307
Let's go to a bigger hospital.

560
00:51:42,307 --> 00:51:44,166
I told you.

561
00:51:44,166 --> 00:51:46,068
That won't make a difference.

562
00:51:46,068 --> 00:51:48,654
Then, do you want to continue on like this?

563
00:51:48,654 --> 00:51:51,424
Are you planning to die on the mountain?

564
00:51:51,424 --> 00:51:53,526
That's not a bad idea.

565
00:51:56,613 --> 00:52:01,217
What about the position at the headquarters in Wonju?

566
00:52:01,217 --> 00:52:02,103
Honey,

567
00:52:02,103 --> 00:52:05,755
why don't you go rest up at the residence?

568
00:52:05,755 --> 00:52:08,024
Let's have a delicious meal together.

569
00:52:12,480 --> 00:52:14,640
A serious fall accident at the Jeonmuk Valley in the Amleung area.
[From Jirisan National Park Office]

570
00:52:18,226 --> 00:52:19,560
I'm sorry, Honey.

571
00:52:19,560 --> 00:52:21,771
But wait for me at the residence.

572
00:52:21,771 --> 00:52:23,656
I'll call you.

573
00:52:26,193 --> 00:52:28,819
I'm really sorry...

574
00:52:28,819 --> 00:52:31,564
but I must return to the mountains.

575
00:52:32,232 --> 00:52:34,350
I'm really sorry.

576
00:52:53,053 --> 00:52:55,104
Did something happen?

577
00:52:56,364 --> 00:52:59,260
The real mountain spirits are going there

578
00:53:01,328 --> 00:53:03,688
...to take care of the mountain.

579
00:53:06,984 --> 00:53:08,985
Ranger Station, Control Room.

580
00:53:08,985 --> 00:53:12,238
A major rock-falling accident occurred at the rocky ridge of Jeonmuk Valley.

581
00:53:12,238 --> 00:53:14,865
A number of illegal hikers are injured.

582
00:53:14,865 --> 00:53:19,500
Rangers from all stations and shelters, mobilize to Jeonmuk Valley.

583
00:53:19,500 --> 00:53:22,970
[Deoksan Temple]

584
00:53:42,202 --> 00:53:43,911
What are these?

585
00:53:48,475 --> 00:53:50,176
What?

586
00:53:51,244 --> 00:53:54,530
Why did they throw all these away in this deep forest?

587
00:53:54,530 --> 00:53:55,865
That's what I'm saying.

588
00:53:55,865 --> 00:53:57,992
Get some help and clean these out.

589
00:53:57,992 --> 00:53:59,894
Yes, Sir.

590
00:54:17,650 --> 00:54:22,030
[Caution]
[Asian black bear protection area]

591
00:54:43,371 --> 00:54:45,290
What are you doing here?

592
00:54:48,043 --> 00:54:50,111
I'm looking for something.

593
00:54:50,111 --> 00:54:52,963
Did you lose something?

594
00:54:52,963 --> 00:54:58,149
The rangers already took all the lost articles near here.

595
00:55:02,257 --> 00:55:04,725
What brings you here?

596
00:55:04,725 --> 00:55:06,352
Here?

597
00:55:06,352 --> 00:55:09,347
This was my hideout when I was little.

598
00:55:10,607 --> 00:55:14,593
We called it the Black Bridge Valley Shelter.

599
00:55:14,593 --> 00:55:17,571
- Then...
- That's right.

600
00:55:17,571 --> 00:55:19,966
This is my hometown.

601
00:55:20,617 --> 00:55:22,910
This is your hometown?

602
00:55:22,910 --> 00:55:24,495
Yup.

603
00:55:26,790 --> 00:55:29,358
You've seen the video, right?

604
00:55:29,358 --> 00:55:31,043
Yes.

605
00:55:31,043 --> 00:55:33,237
What that man said is all wrong.

606
00:55:33,237 --> 00:55:38,993
This village didn't disappear because of cable cars or demolition.

607
00:55:38,993 --> 00:55:44,128
The villagers left because of the ghost lights.

608
00:55:44,128 --> 00:55:46,083
What do you mean?

609
00:55:46,083 --> 00:55:48,750
Whenever something bad happened to the village,

610
00:55:48,750 --> 00:55:51,320
the ghost lights always apeared first.

611
00:55:53,275 --> 00:55:55,734
I heard wild beasts' eyes glow like that

612
00:55:55,734 --> 00:55:58,938
reflected in the light when it's dark.

613
00:56:00,282 --> 00:56:02,241
I saw them with my own eyes this time.

614
00:56:02,241 --> 00:56:06,296
The ones I saw were Asian black bears' eyes.

615
00:56:08,348 --> 00:56:11,200
Back then, there were no bears on the mountain.

616
00:56:22,262 --> 00:56:26,265
Whatever you're looking for, I hope you find it.

617
00:56:26,265 --> 00:56:27,934
- Yes.
- Then.

618
00:57:50,490 --> 00:57:57,360
♫ The same day, it makes me feel smaller ♫

619
00:57:58,450 --> 00:58:04,600
♫ There are people that come to mind when that happens ♫

620
00:58:04,600 --> 00:58:11,800
♫ Clear eyes, and the sincerity in them ♫

621
00:58:12,700 --> 00:58:20,000
♫ Make me smile so I can stand up again ♫

622
00:58:20,000 --> 00:58:26,920
♫ Without you, I wouldn't be here ♫

623
00:58:26,920 --> 00:58:32,210
♫ Now I won't let go the hand I grabbed ♫

624
00:58:32,210 --> 00:58:35,090
[Jirisan]

625
00:58:35,090 --> 00:58:35,978
You know what though?

626
00:58:35,978 --> 00:58:38,480
Today's our one-year anniversary since we met.

627
00:58:38,480 --> 00:58:41,900
If I get the murderer, maybe you'll wake up.

628
00:58:41,900 --> 00:58:44,194
We should let people know what happened in here.

629
00:58:44,194 --> 00:58:45,320
You knew this.

630
00:58:45,320 --> 00:58:47,406
Since when have you known about this?

631
00:58:47,406 --> 00:58:49,450
We weren't the only ones on the mountain that day.

632
00:58:49,450 --> 00:58:50,368
Jung Goo Yeong?

633
00:58:50,368 --> 00:58:52,327
Why did you go to the mountain that day?

634
00:58:52,327 --> 00:58:54,439
It could get too risky for you.

635
00:58:54,439 --> 00:58:55,664
There is a way.

636
00:58:55,664 --> 00:58:57,834
Why are these people together?

637
00:58:57,834 --> 00:58:59,793
How can we? We don't know who it was.

638
00:58:59,793 --> 00:59:03,150
Hyun Jo knew about the murderer.

639
00:59:03,150 --> 00:59:06,620
♫ I'm always by your side, with you ♫
